Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of facial image hallucination using convolutional neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel deep learning model that incorporates identity priors into the learning procedure. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses AI techniques to generate high-resolution facial images from low-resolution inputs. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image processing and enhancement techniques for facial images. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for facial image hallucination.
